    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "I tested something: Currently is possible query by ObjectID\r\n\r\n<img width=\"603\" alt=\"screen shot 2017-03-13 at 23 57 32\" src=\"https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2096101/23878634/db1dd3a4-0848-11e7-8879-b5daa9327701.png\">\r\n\r\nThis picture is using index panel and I get the result.\r\n\r\nSo basically, Need to do the same but from `<InstantSearch/>`\r\n\r\nI saw that the component serialize the widgets urls. \r\n\r\nFor example, if I have a `condition` refinement with `used|new` as value, the url for filter by `new` looks like:\r\n\r\n```\r\nhttps://market.windtoday.co/?refinementList[condition][0]=new\r\n```\r\n\r\nserialized into:\r\n\r\n```\r\nhttps%3A%2F%2Fmarket.windtoday.co%2F%3FrefinementList%5Bcondition%5D%5B0%5D%3Dnew\r\n```\r\n\r\nIn the objectID case, I suppose that is necessary define the way to serialize the objectID value as the backend is expecting it? similar to\r\n\r\n```\r\nhttps://market.windtoday.co/?[objectID]=3566358081\r\n```\r\n",
